Found a potential bug.

RxJS 4 does this:

``` js
var e1 = hot(    '--a---b---c---|');
var inner = cold(  '-1-2-3-4|    ');
var expected =   '---1-2#        ';

var result = e1.concatMap(value => {
  if (value === 'b') {
    throw 'error';
  }
  return inner;
});
```

while RxJS Next does this:

``` js
var e1 = hot(    '--a---b---c---|');
var inner = cold(  '-1-2-3-4|    ');
var expected =   '---1-2-3-4#    ';

var result = e1.concatMap(value => {
  if (value === 'b') {
    throw 'error';
  }
  return inner;
});
```

If we are to mirror RxJS 4's functionality, then it's a bug. But we might also be redefining how concatMap should work.

